P(n)
a_{1}+a_{2}+...+a_{n}=\dfrac{(a_{1}+a_{n})n}{2}, \forall n\in \mathbb N
P(1)
a_{1}=\dfrac{(a_{1}+a_{1})1}{2} \implies a_{1}=\dfrac{2a_{1}}{2} \implies a_{1}=a_{1}
P(1)
P(2)
a_{1}+a_{2}=\dfrac{(a_{1}+a_{2})2}{2} \implies a_{1}+a_{2}=a_{1}+a_{2} 
P(2)
a_{i+1}-a_{i}= r \implies $$a_{k}=a_{k+1}-r
a_{1}+a_{2}+...+a_{k}+a_{k+1}=\dfrac{(a_{1}+a_{k})k}{2}+a_{k+1}
=\dfrac{1}{2}[(a_{1}+a_{k})k+2a_{k+1}]
a_{k}=a_{k+1}-r$ 
 
